name: axios
text:
Joe Biden will face three urgent nuclear challenges upon entering the White House: 
➡️ Arms control with Russia is crumbling
➡️  Iran’s uranium stockpiles are growing
➡️ North Korea is as vexing and threatening as ever
https://t.co/yV3kQKD4GP

name: axios
text:
One ritual of becoming president-elect is the carousel of congratulatory phone calls with other world leaders.

The order in which the calls are returned is watched closely around the world.
https://t.co/q8dajQaSt3

name: axios
text:
Russia’s state-run research institute announced that its COVID-19 vaccine is 92% effective. 

Experts have criticized the lack of transparency around the vaccine and the haste with which the Kremlin approved it, but countries are lining up to gain access. https://t.co/pwcNVZx4W0

name: axios
text: The Ivy League has canceled its winter sports for the 2020-21 season. The announcement comes as states across the U.S. see a surge in new coronavirus cases. https://t.co/CjWSBs2FgF

name: axios
text: Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Wenbin congratulated President-elect Biden and Vice President-elect Harris on their election victory, saying that China "respected the choice of the American people."  https://t.co/e5zK5AIWMY

name: axios
text:
Providing a single dose of a coronavirus vaccine to the world's 7.8 billion people would fill 8,000 747 freighter planes.

But most cargo flies in the holds of passenger aircraft, and one in four airplanes have been grounded during the pandemic. https://t.co/efZwyPked5
